# Shift Monitor Pro — Full Stack

Node.js + MySQL + Vanilla JS frontend.  
Multi-branch employee attendance and shift tracking with 3 roles.

---

## Project Structure

```
shiftmonitor/
├── .env.example              # Copy → .env and fill in values
├── .gitignore
├── package.json
├── database/
│   ├── schema.sql            # Run once to create all tables
│   └── seed.js               # Creates the Super Admin account
├── backend/
│   ├── server.js             # Express entry point
│   ├── config/
│   │   └── db.js             # MySQL connection pool
│   ├── middleware/
│   │   └── auth.js           # JWT verify + role guard
│   ├── controllers/
│   │   ├── authController.js
│   │   ├── branchController.js
│   │   ├── userController.js
│   │   ├── attendanceController.js
│   │   ├── correctionController.js
│   │   ├── shiftController.js
│   │   └── dashboardController.js
│   └── routes/
│       ├── auth.js
│       ├── branches.js
│       ├── users.js
│       ├── attendance.js
│       ├── corrections.js
│       ├── shifts.js
│       └── dashboard.js
└── frontend/
    └── ShiftMonitorPro.html  # Full UI — open in browser
```

---

## Prerequisites

- Node.js v18+
- MySQL 8.0+ (or XAMPP)

---

## Local Setup

### 1. Install MySQL

**Option A — MySQL directly:**  
Download from https://dev.mysql.com/downloads/mysql/

**Option B — XAMPP (easier):**  
Download from https://www.apachefriends.org → start MySQL from the XAMPP control panel.

### 2. Create the database

Open MySQL Workbench (or phpMyAdmin at http://localhost/phpmyadmin) and run:

```sql
-- File: database/schema.sql
-- Either paste into MySQL Workbench and click Run (⚡)
-- Or run from terminal:
mysql -u root -p < database/schema.sql
```

### 3. Install Node dependencies

```bash
cd shiftmonitor
npm install
```

### 4. Configure environment

```bash
# Windows
copy .env.example .env

# Mac / Linux
cp .env.example .env
```

Open `.env` and set:
```
DB_PASSWORD=your_mysql_root_password
JWT_ACCESS_SECRET=<run: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(64).toString('hex'))">
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=<run same command again for a different value>
```

### 5. Seed the Super Admin

```bash
node database/seed.js
```

This prints the admin email and password to the terminal.

### 6. Start the server

```bash
npm run dev     # development (auto-restart with nodemon)
# or
npm start       # production
```

You should see:
```
MySQL pool connected.
Server running on http://localhost:5000
```

### 7. Open the frontend

Open `frontend/ShiftMonitorPro.html` in your browser.  
Or use VS Code's **Live Server** extension (right-click → Open with Live Server).

---

## API Endpoints

### Auth
| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| POST | /api/auth/login | Login |
| POST | /api/auth/refresh | Refresh access token |
| POST | /api/auth/logout | Logout |
| POST | /api/auth/change-password | Change password (auth required) |

### Dashboard
| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | /api/dashboard | Role-aware summary stats |

### Branches (Super Admin only)
| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | /api/branches | List all branches |
| POST | /api/branches | Create branch |
| PUT | /api/branches/:id | Update branch |
| DELETE | /api/branches/:id | Deactivate branch |

### Users / Employees
| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | /api/users | List employees |
| POST | /api/users | Create employee |
| PUT | /api/users/:id | Update employee |
| DELETE | /api/users/:id | Deactivate employee |
| GET | /api/users/me | Get own profile |
| PUT | /api/users/me | Update own profile |

### Attendance
| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | /api/attendance | List records (filterable) |
| GET | /api/attendance/today | Today's records |
| GET | /api/attendance/my-status | Employee's own clock status |
| GET | /api/attendance/stats | Aggregate stats |
| POST | /api/attendance/clock-in | Clock in |
| POST | /api/attendance/clock-out | Clock out |
| PUT | /api/attendance/:id | Manual edit (admin) |

### Corrections
| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | /api/corrections | List correction requests |
| POST | /api/corrections | Submit request |
| PUT | /api/corrections/:id/approve | Approve |
| PUT | /api/corrections/:id/reject | Reject |

### Shifts
| Method | Path | Description |
|--------|------|-------------|
| GET | /api/shifts | List shifts |
| POST | /api/shifts | Create shift |
| PUT | /api/shifts/:id | Update shift |
| DELETE | /api/shifts/:id | Deactivate shift |

---

## Default Credentials

After running `node database/seed.js`:

| Field | Value |
|-------|-------|
| Email | admin@shiftmonitorpro.com |
| Password | Admin@1234 (or SEED_ADMIN_PASSWORD in .env) |

**Change this password immediately after first login.**

---

## Deployment (when ready)

1. **Database:** PlanetScale, Railway MySQL, or AWS RDS
2. **Backend:** Railway, Render, or a VPS (set NODE_ENV=production)
3. **Frontend:** Serve the HTML from the same Node server or Netlify/Vercel

Add this to `server.js` to serve the frontend statically in production:
```js
const path = require('path');
app.use(express.static(path.join(__dirname, '../frontend')));
```

---

## Security Notes

- JWT access tokens expire in 15 minutes
- Refresh tokens are rotated on every use
- Passwords are hashed with bcrypt (cost 12)
- Rate limiting on all routes (200/15min) and login (20/15min)
- Branch admins are strictly scoped to their own branch
- Never commit `.env` to version control